SIMPLE: terrine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Terrine
<hw>Ter*rine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Tureen</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dish or pan, originally of
earthenware, such as those in which various dishes are cooked and
served; esp., an earthenware jar containing some table delicacy and sold
with its contents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A kind of ragout formerly
cooked and served in the same dish; also, a dish consisting of several
meats braised together and served in a terrine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A soup tureen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Territorial</ent>⟦br⟧
